To      all~
Subject Notices and such...~
Text
This is just a friendly reminder to those of you who think we do nothing...
Saenok and I (with an idea from Xenabu) just coded an 'afk message' flag
that works like this:

1: you type 'afk' and get this:
. `&You are now in AFK mode with no message.``

2: You type 'afk This is a test.' and get this:
. `&You are now in AFK mode with '`@This is a test.`&' as your message.``


Characters who send tells to an afk char will get one of the following:

1: `&They are currently AFK: '`@No message`&'.``

2: `&They are currently AFK: '`@This is a test.`&'.``
#2 of course shows whatever message you just typed, not 'This is a test.'

Disclaimer: this is on MY machine, not live code. We'll talk with the B's
and see about getting some more cool sh*t in here.

Brought to you by:
`8V`&o`7r`&l`8in`` - `7[`` `!P`1sycho`` `8A`7d`&m`7i`8n`` `7]`` 
Saenok `&ORE NO KINTAMA: KAZE MO NAI NO NI BURABURA``

Idea credit to : `&Xenabu``
~
