Stamp   953846921
To      all~
Subject "The Great Anime Compromise"~
Text
For those that don't know, I picked that subject title in reference to the post Revolution planning of the Constitution...where the delegates were arguing over going with the Virginia Plan or the New Jersey Plan
In the end, Roger Sherman of Connecticut, came up with a compromise to end the delegates' bickering and satisfy everyone
If it wasn't for this compromise, our American nation would have fallen (OUR meaning AMERICANS not you CANADIANS)
I shall be Roger Sherman. ( this part was just my preamble =P ) 
`1Point One: Experience from Level 73+``
Okay from reading all the ideas posted from all you influential people, I have derived the perfect solution. The cap from level 73 will be removed.
The experience from level 73 till 85 will start to curve. At level 85, the experience cap will begin, making it much harder and strive for the 5 level drive to 90.
Also, from level 73 on, mobs will start dodging/phasing/parrying less so melee will matter.
`2Point Two: PK and Clans``
If one item can be looted from a corpse and the corpse cannot be sacrificed, PK will be enhanced. People will much less safe sit, and more and more will go PK Set and clans will be bigger and more active.
Also, if Dragon Punch (Ryu's move from Street Fighter) was just a physical attack, it would balance the (Any Race) Monk vs Cyborg (Any Class) R@ping. Or Cyborgs can be changed to not be vulnerable to fire. For example, its description in 'HELP CYB
ORG' (sorry for the cutoff) a Cyborg is "like a Terminator". I'm sure most of you saw the movie and how flame and fire and bullets and heat could not stop him. The only thing that did was the frost (which makes sense for Cyborgs to be vulnerable t
o)(sorry again for the cutoff) and the molten metal in Terminator 2. ANY THING will melt in molten lava. Why make only Cyborgs who are made of metal vulnerable to fire?
Dragon Punch let's say, is stronger than circle. What if Dragon-kin's were still vulnerable to piercing and someone hit them with backstabs. Ouch right? Its that way for Cyborgs, except that Dragonkins have more HP.
And cskills...okay...3k through sanctuary? Should I go any further? Only leaders getting them? Don't ya think it's dang hard killing Clan Leaders already considering that almost all PK Clan Leaders are either Espers or Demons, now they got MAD Csk
ills? I'm not PK though...but I've heard various people complaining...
`3Point Three: New AQEQ``
The new AQEQ isn't really all that good...For example a Ring of Wisdom and a Ring of Talpa takes time to get, but they do not add up to the stats that two Rings of Powers that Julia easily gives so they aren't really worth while...People have true
sight and that lasts a while so why get the rings for their extra flags? Why not make AQEQ worthwhile for example by making the Rings 10 HITroll and the other 10 DAMroll instead of 8?
Also, WHAT IF, you could autoquest for 10,000 QP to buy ONE practice? Level 90 people can't level further and usually have a lot of spare time, especially NON-PK so they often quest. What if you have all the AQEQ or you have all the ones you want?
There'd be no point in questing anymore. Why not be able to buy practices through QP? That wasn't a bad idea...10k QP is a lot and is a challenge...you'd need 100k QP just to be enough for one train. I doubt it would unbalance PK by much.
I mean who here hasn't seen Osumi going into the void and posing to get back out over and over again because he has nothing to do but (SEE POINT 4)
Also, why not add another piece? It could be called a "Master Key" which can open any lock in the MUD. Usually you're roaming around but then you find some place that needs a key that you don't have. You'd have to find the mob that loads it. Not a
nymore...with this handy dandy key, you can open the door! It could have the stats of a Sailormoon's Protection but be a key worn as a light. (hehe)
It'd be an illuminated, glowing key. It could be worth 2000 QP.
