atcaully what the government is developing currently are Hardsuits, (light powered armor) for deep space use, because the suits we have now just are not cutting it,
ground based versions will most likely be Motor Asissted, and that will completly rock, because then the suit will be doing the work your muscles would normally do
they've gotten pretty far along, last I've heard... and altho large mechanical suits would be infesable, 
because of that pesky Square Cubed Law... (everytime you square the bodysurface, you Cube the mass. and thats *ALOT* of mass) 
so I doubt we're going to see MS Gundams running around *anytime* soon.... 
but oh well, technology is making leaps and bounds past what we're readyfor.... 
not to mention the goverments also working on gravity reduction (suposidly) 
by using supercooled mercury plasma.....
anyway. thats just all the rumors I've heard...

forgive the messyness of this note, 
Kyosami Asagiri..... 
~
