saying its ala "Knight Sabers" would be a strech I wouldn't even attempt... 
but the general purpose is to build a more durable functional aerospace suit, which will be
*fully* articulate in its range of motions, and a ground based version would probly be something more along the lines of simple infintry inhancement, so they can be better protected and carry larger caliber weapons. 
giving them a chance against larger artiliery units, like tanks. 
and what I said about the Square Cubed law *is* true, it is completly impossible with our current technology to build a humanoid larger than 8 feet tall, 
Bipedal forms are just not very stable, and at that point the mass of the struture exeeds its weight bearing capacity
~
