Subject Note spam! Weee!~
Text
One day, an Amish family went to the crowded city to sell their wares. Being unfamiliar with the metallic jungle, they soon wandered off to a high-rise hotel.
As the rest of the family wandered away to gawk at the weirdly dressed people and to stare at the various stores, father and son noticed a pair of shiny doors that opened and closed with a touch of a button.
The boy asked his father what it was, and his father answered: "Son, I've never seen such a contraption all my life."
Just than, a small, disheveled and sour-looking grandmotherly lady walked up to it, and punched the button. The magic doors swung open, and she stepped into the small room.
They watched in fascination as the light went from one to thiry seven, than down again. When the door opened once more, a glamorous, busty blonde walked out, smiling.
The man and son were dumbfounded. Finally, the father said: "Son, go fetch your mother."
~
